          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-The operation of a thermal neutron time-of-flight",
                " spectrometer-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CHOPS"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Slow chopper.",
                " Rotating laminated Cd-Al shutter.Double-sided mirror",
                " attached to shutter. P.E. cell trigger.",
                " Observed gate lengths were constant to 0.5% over",
                " period of 1 hour.Average motor speed was constant to",
                " at least 0.5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "THCOL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Thermal column of the Bepo reactor. Collimated.",
                " Modified bismuth filter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Maxwellian distribution function was fitted to short",
                " wavelength side of spectrum. Long wavelength side is",
                " increased relative to short one. Discontinuity in",
                " spectrum at 4 Angstrom is due to 1001-planes in",
                " graphite. For neutron wavelengths > 6 Angstrom an",
                " additional short length of filter material was placed",
                " outside the pile shield.",
                " Density spectrum is smooth Maxwellian distribution."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Gold plates of thickness 0.992,0.950,0.954 and 0.948",
                " gm/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight. 358 cm and 204 cm path lengths."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Transmissions of combinations of four gold",
                " plates for measurement at energy range 0.001 eV to",
                " 0.1 eV.",
                " Three sources of background were considered:",
                " - stray neutrons coming from all directions, reduced",
                "  by B4C and paraffin wax shield,",
                " - epi-cadmium neutrons in beam, only slightly",
                "   attenuated by shutter,",
                " - neutrons scattered by collimating slits, shutter",
                "   and samples.",
                " Shutter was set running at synchronous speed and all",
                " pulses from detector were recorded for two-minute with",
                " sample in beam and then with it out.",
                " Test of spectrum and counting rate at 300 micro-sec/m",
                "-a. for normal condition,",
                "-b. with graphite block reduced intensity by factor",
                " about 15,",
                "-c. with boron glass plate reduced intensity by same",
                " factor, changing spectrum to give factor 4 between",
                " the counting rates in first and last channels,",
                " showed that various measurements agree better than 1%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " BF3 proportional counter as neutron detector.",
                " 7 cm diameter cylinder filled to pressure of 30 cm Hg",
                " with natural BF3."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
